# Scott Dashboard — environment variables (no secrets in git)
# Copy the section you need into a local file (see docs/ENVIRONMENTS.md).

# =============================================================================
# PRODUCTION (live users — Netlify `main` branch + production Supabase project)
# =============================================================================
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROD_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-production-anon-or-publishable-key

# =============================================================================
# STAGING (safe testing — Netlify `develop` branch + staging Supabase project)
# =============================================================================
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_STAGING_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-staging-anon-or-publishable-key

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local development: use STAGING keys only (never prod in day-to-day dev).
# See .env.development.example → copy to .env.development
# Optional: .env.staging.example → copy to .env.staging for `npm run dev:staging`
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
